Grouped_Utterances: I’d like to discuss how to handle criticism, especially since I’m putting my work out there.
It felt validating. I’m starting to feel more confident about my work. I have, and it stung at first. I took it personally, but I’ve learned to separate myself from the work.

I’ve been good! I stuck to my goal of dedicating time to my personal project. It felt great! I was able to get a lot done, and I even experimented with some new techniques. I played around with lighting and angles. It opened up a new perspective for me. I was pleasantly surprised! Some of the shots turned out better than I expected. Yes, I shared some photos with my friend who’s an artist, and she gave me some positive feedback. Yes! I’ve been jotting down ideas and locations that resonate with me.
Thank you! I feel like I’m making progress.

I think I want to keep challenging myself with new projects and techniques. I want to create a series that tells a story about my transition to LA. I’m thinking of capturing different aspects of my life here, like the people I meet and the places I visit. I guess I’ll remind myself that everyone has their own story, and mine is just as valid. Yes, I think that would help. I want to grow, not feel defeated. I’ll try to remind myself to consider the feedback objectively and see if there’s something I can learn from it.
